# Trim the published archive. The example's per-platform scaffolding
# (Xcode projects, gradle wrappers, app icons, CMake) is generated, not
# source, and inflates the package to ~10x its real size. Excluding it
# ships only the example's Dart source. A consumer regenerates the
# platform folders by running `flutter create .` in example/, then
# `flutter run` — the example remains runnable on all platforms.
#
# .pubignore (not .gitignore) so these stay tracked in git but absent
# from the pub.dev archive.
example/android/
example/ios/
example/macos/
example/linux/
example/windows/
